    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-03-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 11513/27.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Bryan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 381, of the 17th ultimo, in which you state that you have been
                    requested by the minister of foreign affairs of Portugal to convey sincere
                    acknowledgments to Congress of the resolutions of condolence passed <pb
                        facs="0794" n="692" xml:id="pg_692"/> by the United States Senate and House
                    of Representatives in view of the assassination of the King and Crown Prince of
                    Portugal.</p>
                <p>Copies of your dispatch have been transmitted to the Vice President and the
                    Speaker of the House of Representatives for the information of the Senate and
                    House of Representatives.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
